GOAL: surface real-content divergences the existing gates miss — the gates use
synthetic content + a CID22 subset (real-image default presets 2/6/10); this
sweep broadens to 3 real corpora INCLUDING SCREEN content (a class no gate has),
across preset {0,6,10,13} x qp {5,20,32,48,63} x bit-depth {8,10}.

CORPORA (each image encoded at a 512x512 box; clic/screen CENTER-CROPPED via the
new identity_run `crop:` prefix so preset-0 — the SB128-triggering primary config
— stays tractable while exercising each corpus's real content statistics):
  cid22  15 imgs  CID22-512 photo (native 512, file:)
  clic   12 imgs  clic2025 photo (~2.7MP, crop:512) — a different photo distribution
  screen 10 imgs  gb82-sc SCREEN/UI/text (crop:512) — NEW axis, no prior gate

RESULT: 1090/1480 byte-identical (73.6%); 310 DIFFERS; 80 rs-err (a bd10 PANIC — see
below; FIXED this branch). Every port stream that encoded is aomdec-DECODABLE.

