FIVE DISTINCT DIVERGENCE GROUPS (representative first-divergence localization):

1. PHOTO preset-0 (bd8) — UNIVERSAL, ~85% of p0 cells. First divergence = FH
   `loop_filter_level` (the deblock-level FULL SEARCH `pick_filter_levels_full_search`,
   preset<=5 only; p6-13 use the closed-form from-Q picker => clean). Pre-deblock
   recon SSE differs only ~0.08% (Y) from C => a TINY real-content MD near-tie
   perturbs the recon the post-MD filter searches read. KNOWN class (docs/
   bd10-port-map.md "three post-MD searches"; CLAUDE.md:962). NEW: mapped as the
   universal bd8 p0 photo root across a wide corpus (was only bd10-documented).
   Rep cell: cid22 1459534 p0 q63 bd8 (FH loop_filter_level[2] C=16 Rust=14).

2. PHOTO preset-0 (bd10) — the tile diverges at OP 0 (first partition symbol,
   CDF8:s3 vs v0): a MAJOR MD divergence (documented bd10 full-RD funnel root,
   30-50% recon divergence, docs/bd10-port-map.md). Distinct from group 1 (bd8's
   MD is nearly identical; bd10's diverges at the first block).

3. clic p6 bd10 q5 — FH byte-identical, TILE Wiener LR-taps diverge (bd10 Wiener
   loop-restoration tap search near-tie at LOW qp on textured content). NOT covered
   by any gate (bd10_photo_gate p6 tests only q{12,32,55} on 3 CID22 imgs). GATE GAP.

4. SCREEN preset-0/6 (bd8) — the KEY NEW FIND. Screen diverges ~50-86% at p0/p6
   (where palette/screen-content-tools are active) but is 100% IDENTICAL at p10/p13
   (palette OFF at M9). Root = PALETTE over-picking / palette-vs-regular RD near-tie:
   on graph p6 the port codes palette on 968 blocks vs C's 252 (over-picks). Known
   class (svtav1 memory svtav1-71-palette-overpicking-root.md, aom KB-P29). NEW:
   first byte-test of palette on REAL screenshots (palette was only decode-tested on
   synthetic "stripes"). SC-DETECTION itself is correct (codec_wiki/gmessages, where
   C uses no palette, are byte-identical). Rep: graph p6 bd8 q32 tile op 41.

5. SCREEN preset-0/6 (bd10) — PANIC (80 rs-err cells, all screen+bd10+p{0,6} on the
   8 palette-triggering shots). Index-out-of-bounds in the bd10 leaf search:
   encode_frame_420 -> encode_fixed_tree -> decide_leaf_rect -> evaluate_leaf ->
   tx_unit_hbd (leaf_funnel.rs `residual.push(src[..]-pred[..])`). A surviving palette
   candidate reaches the bd10 full-RD stage with a u8 w*h palette prediction where the
   hbd path indexes a u16 buffer => OOB. A PANIC ON THE PUBLIC API for bd10 screen
   content. FIXED this branch (leaf_funnel.rs: gate palette injection on `!bd10_funnel`
   — bd8-inert, inert on all non-screen bd10 gates; converts the panic to graceful
   non-palette decodable output). Byte-exact bd10 palette remains a future #71 port.

NON-FINDINGS (clean): p10/p13 = 100% identical on ALL corpora incl. screen (390/390
each); SC detection matches C on real screenshots; all encoded streams decodable.
